This paper involves the development of a reinforcement learning-based conversational agent to assist users in subjective search tasks. The paper discusses the use of a stochastic virtual user to efficiently sample user behavior for training the agent, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of conversational data and the development of a context-preserving architecture suggest a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper's focus on search tasks suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
